  "color_desc": {
    "kicker": "The color · in plain words",
    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Driftwood sits in the heart of the gray spectrum for Duration. It reads as a clean charcoal in direct sun and softens to a near-black on cloudy or shaded elevations. That tonal range is the reason it dominates the dimensional asphalt category nationally.",
      "Owens Corning uses a tight blend of dark gray and faint blue-gray granules to keep the surface visually alive. The result is a roof that reads as a clean architectural line from the street and a textured surface up close.",
      "Pairs cleanly with white, cream, navy, sage, and warm terra-cotta sidings. Almost any house color works underneath it."
    ],
